@startuml Arbitrage_DatabaseFlow
!theme plain
title Match Monitor - Arbitrage Detection - Database Flow (All SPs)

!define DB_COLOR #E3F2FD
!define SP_COLOR #FFF9C4
!define TABLE_COLOR #C8E6C9

' Databases
database "CTS_DataCenter" DB_COLOR {
  rectangle "SystemParameter" as SysParam TABLE_COLOR
  rectangle "MatchMonitorRuleSetting" as RuleSetting TABLE_COLOR
  rectangle "MatchMonitorStagingArbitrageNonLive\n(Pool 2004)" as Staging TABLE_COLOR
  rectangle "CTSMatchMonitor" as Match TABLE_COLOR
  rectangle "CTSMatchMonitorDetail" as Detail TABLE_COLOR
  rectangle "Association Tables" as Assoc TABLE_COLOR
}

' Stored Procedures
rectangle "**Stored Procedures**" SP_COLOR {
  rectangle "SP 1: RuleArbitrage_Get\n(Get staging matches)" as SP1 #FFEB3B
  rectangle "SP 2: RuleArbitrage_Process\n(Detect and process)" as SP2 #FFEB3B
  rectangle "SP 3: RuleArbitrage_Complete\n(Save results)" as SP3 #FFEB3B
  rectangle "SP 4: RuleArbitrage_TransClean\n(Clean staging)" as SP4 #FFEB3B
  rectangle "SP 5: Association_Device_Get\n(Device detection)" as SP5 #FFC107
  rectangle "SP 6: Association_AI_Get\n(AI detection)" as SP6 #FFC107
  rectangle "SP 7: Association_IP_Get\n(IP detection)" as SP7 #FFC107
}

' SP1: Get staging matches
SP1 -down-> SysParam : READ LastScannedSequenceID\n(ParameterID = 128)
SP1 -down-> RuleSetting : READ TimeStep, CustStake\n(RuleGroupID = 5, Reason = 2)
SP1 -down-> Match : READ old GroupID\n(WHERE Reason = 'AR')
SP1 -down-> Staging : **SELECT** matches\nWHERE SequenceID > LastScannedSequenceID\nGROUP BY MatchID, ScoreDiff, BettypeID, BetID, HDP\nLIMIT 5000

note bottom of SP1
  **Input:**
  - @ip_LiveIndicator = 0 (NonLive only)
  
  **Output:**
  - MatchStagingList (grouped)
  - @op_MaxSequenceID
  
  **Logic:**
  1. Get LastScannedSequenceID from SystemParameter
  2. Get rule settings (TimeStep, CustStake)
  3. Read old GroupID from CTSMatchMonitor
  4. Query staging table for new matches
  5. Group by match characteristics
  6. Return grouped matches + MaxSequenceID
end note

' SP5, SP6, SP7: Association Detection
SP2 -up-> SP5 : **CALL** for each customer group\n(Device detection)
SP2 -up-> SP6 : **CALL** for each customer group\n(AI detection)
SP2 -up-> SP7 : **CALL** for each customer group\n(IP detection)

SP5 -down-> Assoc : **SELECT** Device associations
SP6 -down-> Assoc : **SELECT** AI associations
SP7 -down-> Assoc : **SELECT** IP associations

note top of SP5
  **Association Detection (3 Criteria):**
  
  SP5: Device
  - Input: CTSCustIDList
  - Logic: Same DeviceID
  - Output: Grouped customers
  
  SP6: AI
  - Input: CTSCustIDList
  - Logic: AI pattern matching
  - Output: Grouped customers
  
  SP7: IP
  - Input: CTSCustIDList
  - Logic: Same IP address
  - Output: Grouped customers
end note

' SP2: Process Rule
SP2 -down-> Staging : **SELECT** tickets\nWHERE SequenceID IN (...)\nAND CustID IN (CustGroup)

note bottom of SP2
  **Input:**
  - @ip_LiveIndicator = 0
  - @ip_MatchID, @ip_ScoreDiff, @ip_BettypeID, @ip_BetID, @ip_HDP
  - @ip_SequenceIDList (from SP1)
  - @ip_CustGroup (JSON: CustID + GroupID from association)
  
  **Logic:**
  1. Parse CustGroup JSON
  2. Get all tickets for customers in group
  3. Time-based grouping (TimeGroupID = TransDateToSecond / TimeStep)
  4. Check opposite bets (GROUP BY Betteam, HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT Betteam) > 1)
  5. Validate stake threshold (SUM(Stake) >= MinStake per customer)
  6. Check Agent customers (Alpha/Maxbet)
  7. Build result groups
  
  **Output:**
  - CompleteMatches (detected arbitrage groups)
  - ReprocessMatches (need more processing)
end note

' SP3: Complete
SP3 -down-> Match : **INSERT** detected matches\n(Reason = 'AR')
SP3 -down-> Detail : **INSERT** ticket details

note bottom of SP3
  **Input:**
  - @ip_LiveIndicator = 0
  - @ip_TransGroupJson (from merged results)
  - @ip_MaxSequenceID
  - Match info (MatchID, ScoreDiff, BettypeID, BetID, HDP)
  
  **Logic:**
  1. Parse TransGroupJson
  2. INSERT into CTSMatchMonitor:
     - MatchID, ScoreDiff, BettypeID, BetID, HDP
     - GroupID (unique)
     - Reason = 'AR'
     - TransIDList, CustIDList
  3. INSERT into CTSMatchMonitorDetail:
     - All tickets in group
     - Link to CTSMatchMonitor via MatchID+GroupID
  
  **Tables Updated:**
  - CTSMatchMonitor (match level)
  - CTSMatchMonitorDetail (ticket level)
end note

' SP4: Clean
SP4 -down-> Staging : **DELETE** processed tickets\nWHERE SequenceID <= MaxSequenceID

note bottom of SP4
  **Input:**
  - @ip_LiveIndicator = 0
  - @ip_MaxSequenceID
  
  **Logic:**
  1. DELETE from MatchMonitorStagingArbitrageNonLive
  2. WHERE SequenceID <= MaxSequenceID
  3. Free space for next batch
  
  **Purpose:**
  - Clean processed tickets
  - Prevent duplicate processing
  - Maintain staging table size
end note

' Flow annotations
note as N1
  **Complete Flow Sequence:**
  
  1. SP1: Get Staging Matches
     └─ Read: SystemParameter, RuleSetting, Staging
     └─ Output: MatchStagingList + MaxSequenceID
  
  2. Association Detection (3 SPs in parallel)
     ├─ SP5: Device detection
     ├─ SP6: AI detection
     └─ SP7: IP detection
     └─ Output: CustGroup JSON (CustID + GroupID)
  
  3. SP2: Process Rule (Round 1 + Round 2)
     ├─ Read: Staging tickets for CustGroup
     ├─ Time-based grouping
     ├─ Opposite bets check
     ├─ Stake threshold validation
     └─ Output: CompleteMatches + ReprocessMatches
  
  4. SP3: Complete (Save Results)
     ├─ Merge all CompleteMatches
     ├─ Assign unique GroupID
     ├─ INSERT: CTSMatchMonitor (Reason='AR')
     └─ INSERT: CTSMatchMonitorDetail
  
  5. SP4: Clean Staging
     └─ DELETE processed tickets from staging
end note

' Table details
note right of Staging
  **MatchMonitorStagingArbitrageNonLive**
  (Pool 2004)
  
  Source: Insert Ticket Detail job
  Frequency: Every 5 minutes
  
  Key Fields:
  - SequenceID (incremental)
  - MatchID, ScoreDiff, BettypeID, BetID, HDP
  - CustID, Stake, Betteam
  - TransDate, TransID
  - SubscriberID (Agent detection)
end note

note right of Match
  **CTSMatchMonitor**
  
  Stores detected arbitrage matches
  
  Key Fields:
  - MatchID, GroupID (PK)
  - Reason = 'AR' (Arbitrage)
  - ScoreDiff, BettypeID, BetID, HDP
  - TransIDList (comma-separated)
  - CustIDList (comma-separated)
  - InsertTime
end note

note right of Detail
  **CTSMatchMonitorDetail**
  
  Stores individual tickets
  
  Key Fields:
  - MatchID, GroupID, TransID (PK)
  - CustID, Stake, Betteam
  - Odds, TransDate
  - Reason = 'AR'
end note

@enduml

